there are 3-flow control statements
-------------------------------------------
1)conditional statements
	if, if else,switch
	
	if (boolean condition) // condition must return either true or false
	{
	true body;
	}
	else
	{
	false body;
	}
	
--> For if condition we can directly pass boolean values as arguments
--> Curly braces are optional but with out braces its possible to take only one statement i.e syso	
Switch case
--> for case labels its perfectly allowed expressions like below

E.g
case 10+10: syso("xyz");
break;
case 10*2: syso("abc");
break;
case 10/5: syso("pqr");
break;

--> case labels must be unique
--> Inside switch default statement is optional
--> Inside switch Cases statements are also optional
--> Finally Inside switch both cases and default statements are optional
--> Inside Switch, you cannot declare independent statements, if declared it should be either of under cases or default: statements

E.g 
{
byte b=10;
Switch(b)
{
syso("some");
}
}



	
2)iteration statements
	while,for,do while
	
3)transfer statements
	goto,break,continue,try block,return		